This is basically just a fork of http://code.google.com/p/pelops/ that's been mavenized.

The following steps will build and publish pelops to you local repo:
1. git clone git@github.com:danwashusen/pelops.git pelops
2. cd pelops
3. mvn clean install

To use pelops in a maven project:
1. Deploy pelops to your local repo using the steps above
2. Add the following repository to project's repositories:
<repository>
  <id>pelops-mvn</id>
  <name>Pelops Maven Repo</name>
  <url>http://github.com/danwashusen/pelops/raw/master/lib</url>
  <snapshots>
    <enabled>false</enabled>
  </snapshots>
</repository>
3. Add the following dep to you project:
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.wyki</groupId>
  <artifactId>pelops</artifactId>
  <version>0.804-SNAPSHOT</version> 
</dependency>
4. Start using pelops
